headline: Morgan Stanley Real Estate Investing Acquires MorningStar Denver Senior Living Portfolio for $305 Million
summary: NEW YORK, December 04, 2025--Morgan Stanley Investment Management and MorningStar Senior Living (MorningStar) announced today that investment funds managed by Morgan Stanley Real Estate Investing (MSREI) have acquired a MorningStar senior housing portfolio from Kayne Anderson Real Estate for $305 million. The portfolio is comprised of 463 units across three communities near Denver. MorningStar, a leading senior housing operator based in Denver, will continue to operate the communities.

headline: BAC Opens Door to Crypto in Managed Portfolios: What Does This Mean?
summary: Bank of America to let advisers recommend 1-4% crypto in their client portfolios from 2026, marking a major shift in its wealth strategy.

headline: Morgan Stanley Considers Offloading Some of Its Data-Center Exposure
summary: SRTs backed by data-center exposure are still a nascent slice of the credit-risk transfer market, where banks hedge their credit exposure, manage capital ratios and free up balance-sheet capacity for more lending by selling credit-linked notes to institutional investors.  Morgan Stanley is also exploring other ways to hedge or syndicate part of its data-center risk, the people said, and there is no guarantee the early-stage SRT talks will result in a deal.

headline: Has Morgan Stanley’s 216% Five Year Surge Left Much Upside On The Table?
summary: If you are wondering whether Morgan Stanley is still attractive after its huge run, or if you are turning up late to the party, this breakdown will help you assess whether the current share price makes sense. The stock has climbed to around $173.72, logging gains of roughly 3.4% over the last week, 6.2% over the last month, 39.2% year to date, 37.4% over 1 year, 120.3% over 3 years and 216.6% over 5 years, which naturally raises the question of how much upside is left from here.
